citation.title: The Edwards to Gulf Conservation Blueprint - Habitat Management Prioritization

resourceInfo.abstract:
Prioritization for maintenance of intact habitat (i.e., habitat quality rating of Good or Very Good), based on local scale ecological integrity, degree of threats faced, potential conservation opportunities, and conservation value of surrounding landscape. In contrast to ecological integrity ratings; threat, opportunity and landscape rankings are largely based on the range of values of any given indicator across the geography, sorted by quantile. There are some exceptions, particularly for indicators used to develop threat rankings (e.g., urban development risk). 

Prioritization for restoration of degraded habitat (i.e., habitat quality rating of Fair or Poor), based on local scale ecological integrity, potential conservation opportunities, and conservation value of surrounding landscape. Threat rankings were not included because the habitat evaluated here is already in a degraded state. In contrast to ecological integrity ratings; threat, opportunity and landscape rankings are largely based on the range of values of any given indicator across the geography, sorted by quantile. 

EEMS is a tree-based, fuzzy logic modeling system, where output values range from -1 to +1, indicating whether a given output is entirely FALSE or TRUE, respectively. Indicators with rankings of High or Very High either refer to the top two quarters of rankings, or fuzzy values > 0 (where quantiles are not used). Indicators with rankings of Low or Medium either refer to the bottom two quarters of rankings, or fuzzy values < 0 (where quantiles are not used). For overall restoration rankings, we used five categories (i.e., quintiles) instead of four categories (i.e., quartiles), creating a new category (‘Not Priority’) that refers to the lowest ranked 20% of potential habitat.
resourceInfo.purpose: Feature class generated by combining three subcomponents using a UNION (i.e., Boolean mean) operator in the Environmental Evaluation Modeling System (EEMS): Human Development Index, Habitat Amount and Connectivity (HAC), and Habitat Quality (HQ).
credit: Tarbox B, IP Kelly, and J Jensen. 2019. The Edwards to Gulf Conservation Blueprint; spatially explicit decision support tools for the San Antonio, Guadalupe, and Lower Colorado River watersheds. Texas State University, San Marcos, TX.

Ranking of participation in TPWD and USFWS incentive programs, based on fuzzy conversion of MEAN_PROGR. Values range from -1 to +1, indicating low (bottom quartile) to very high (top quartile).

Ranking of regional connectivity, derived by combining High_Current_Fz and High_ProtCurrent_Fz with a UNION operator. Values range from -1 to +1, indicating low (< -0.5), medium (<0), high (>0), very high (>0.5).
Ranking of regional connectivity of the given habitat, based on fuzzy conversion of CS_Current. Values range from -1 to +1, indicating low (bottom quartile) to very high (top quartile).
Ranking of implementation of relevant EQIP practices, based on fuzzy conversion of MEAN_EQIPA. Values range from -1 to +1, indicating low (bottom quartile) to very high (top quartile).
Ranking of implementation of relevant EQIP practices, based on fuzzy conversion of MEAN_EQIPP. Values range from -1 to +1, indicating low (bottom quartile) to very high (top quartile).

Ranking of implementation of relevant EQIP practices, derived by combining High_EQIPAcres_Fz and High_EQIPParcels_Fz with a UNION operator. Values range from -1 to +1, indicating low (< -0.5), medium (<0), high (>0), very high (>0.5).
Ranking of floodplain forest ecological integrity at the subwatershed scale. Values range from -1 to +1, indicating low (bottom quartile) to very high (top quartile).

Ranking of overall landscape conservation value for floodplain forests, derived by combining Hi_FFEcoIntHUC_Fz, Hi_RvrEcoIntHUC_Fz, and Hi_Connectivity_Fz with a UNION operator. Values range from -1 to +1, indicating low (bottom quartile) to very high (top quartile).

Ranking of overall habitat maintenance prioritization for floodplain forests, derived by combining Hi_FF_Landscape_Fz, Hi_FF_Threats_Fz, High_FF_Opportunity_Fz, and High_FF_Ec with a UNION operator. Values range from -1 to +1, indicating not priority (bottom quintile) to very high (top quintile).

Ranking of threats faced by floodplain forests, derived by combining Hi_SubRisk_Fz and Hi_Wtdrwls_Fz with a UNION operator. Values range from -1 to +1, indicating low (< -0.5), medium (<0), high (>0), very high (>0.5).

Ranking of overall incentive program participation, derived by combining Hi_EQIP_Fz and Hi_CntyParticipation_Fz with a UNION operator. Values range from -1 to +1, indicating low (< -0.5), medium (<0), high (>0), very high (>0.5).

Ranking of potential partner interest, based on fuzzy conversion of PriorityAr. Values range from -1 to +1, indicating low (no priority areas), medium (1 priority area), high (2 priority areas), very high (3+ priority areas).
Ranking of change in property sizes, based on fuzzy conversion of MEAN_CHA_1. Values range from -1 to +1, indicating low (bottom quartile) to very high (top quartile).
Ranking of regional connectivity of the given habitat, based on fuzzy conversion of CS_ProtCur. Values range from -1 to +1, indicating low (< -0.9), medium (<0), high (>0), very high (>0.9).

Ranking of major river ecological integrity at the subwatershed scale, based on fuzzy conversion of High_RvrEc. Values range from -1 to +1, indicating low (bottom quartile) to very high (top quartile).

Ranking of subdivision risk, derived by combining Hi_PropChange_Fz and Hi_ValChange_Fz with a UNION operator. Values range from -1 to +1, indicating low (< -0.5), medium (<0), high (>0), very high (>0.5).
Ranking of change in property values, based on fuzzy conversion of MEAN_CHANG. Values range from -1 to +1, indicating low (bottom quartile) to very high (top quartile).
Ranking of projected change in water withdrawals, based on fuzzy conversion of Wtdrw_Chng. Values range from -1 to +1, indicating low (bottom quartile) to very high (top quartile).
